|19,74
     A parameter placeholder appears in the heading of a procedure or func-
tion declaration.  It stands for an argument that will be passed to the
subprogram when it is called.
     The parameter declaration gives the name of the parameter and its
type.  The name of the parameter must follow the usual rules for Pascal
names and must be different from every name inside the defined subprogram.
However, it can be the same as a name defined outside the subprogram.
     Parameters may be value parameters, var parameters, or formal
parameters.
|mFor more, choose
|iDo nothing,nop
|iProcedure declarations,Hpnode/procedure
|iFunction declarations,Hpnode/function
|iValue parameters,Hpnode/parameter
|iVar parameters,Hpnode/var_paramete
|iFormal function parameters,Hpnode/function_par
|iFormal procedure parameters,Hpnode/procedure_pa
|p
